# Excalidraw Architecture

## State Management
- Custom state via `actionManager` — **NOT** Redux, Zustand, MobX, or Recoil
- State updates: `actionManager.dispatch()` ONLY
- State type: `AppState` (packages/excalidraw/types.ts)
- NEVER mutate state directly — always create new state objects
- Per-instance isolation via Jotai atoms (see `editor-jotai.ts`) — Jotai is used internally, do NOT replace it with another state library

## Rendering
- Canvas-based rendering via RoughJS — **NOT** DOM-based
- DO NOT use react-konva, fabric.js, pixi.js, or any other canvas library
- Multi-layer canvas architecture: static scene, interactive scene, new-element scene
- SVG export uses separate rendering path (`staticSvgScene.ts`)

## Monorepo Structure
- `packages/excalidraw/` — core React component library (published to npm)
- `packages/element/` — element types and operations
- `packages/math/` — geometry utilities (pure functions, no side effects)
- `packages/common/` — shared constants and types
- `packages/utils/` — helper functions
- `excalidraw-app/` — full-featured web application

## Dependencies
- No new npm packages without explicit approval
- Check `packages/utils/` and `packages/common/` before adding external helpers
- Build order matters: common → math → element → excalidraw → excalidraw-app

## How to verify
- Search for `new Redux` or `createStore` — should find zero
- Search for direct state mutations (e.g., `this.state.elements =`) — should find zero
- All state changes go through `actionManager` or existing Jotai atom setters
- No react-konva/fabric.js/pixi.js imports exist
- Jotai is used for per-instance isolation — do NOT add Redux/Zustand/MobX/Recoil as replacement
